Instead of writing one sun simulator to rule them all, what if we made:

plaintext
Copy
Edit
{sun_core(1000).pressure_fusion().gamma_burst()},
{sun_layer1(300).hydro_sheen().plasma_storm()},
{sun_layer2(200).magnetic_waves().xray_spikes()},
{sun_field().solar_wind().ejecta()},
Each one of these:

Describes a real part of the Sun

Can be simulated, visualized, or affected

Can be tested or mutated separately

Can be public, sharable, contestable
